    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="938"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d938">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/6–1447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-09T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>845. For Adler from State and Treas. It is thought that a loan for currency
                    stabilization is not possible at this stage, re Embtel 1301, June 14. Such a
                    loan would, in any case, require Congressional action. Recognized here that
                    reintroduction [of] silver coins may ultimately provide means of achieving
                    stabilization, but considered that (1) no monetary measure could have
                    appreciable effect in the face of continued massive deficit spending, and, (2)
                    as proposal sketched in Central Bank Governor’s memorandum<note n="94"
                        xml:id="d938fn1">See footnote 72, <ref target="#pg_1135">p.
                        1135</ref>.</note> indicates, if adopted flight from <hi rend="italic"
                        >fapi</hi> might be more seriously accentuated. Your comments requested.
                    [State and Treasury.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
